"children":[
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_nr_s17_0",
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"d4c168",
"children":[
"Myopathies typically present with symmetric weakness of the proximal muscles."
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"47b5f7",
"children":[
"Normal sensory and reflex examination differentiates myopathy from neuropathy."
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"0b037f",
"children":[
"Serum ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"creatine kinase",
"children":[
"CK"
]
},
" level is elevated and falls in response to treatment."
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"c4f934",
"children":[
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"electromyography",
"children":[
"EMG"
]
},
" confirms the presence of myopathic changes (low amplitude, short duration, and polyphasic motor unit potentials)."
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"aa2582",
"children":[
"See Rheumatology chapter for more detailed information on the inflammatory myopathies (polymyositis, dermatomyositis, inclusion body myositis)."
]
},
{
"type":"inline-wrap",
"wrapId":"1",
"contentIds":[
"mk19_bb_nr_s17_inline_t1"
],
"forceOpen":true
},
{
"type":"heading",
"class":"tricked",
"children":[
"Don't Be Tricked"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"class":"tricked",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"215cd3",
"children":[
"Lipophilic statins (atorvastatin, simvastatin, and lovastatin) have a higher propensity to cause statin myopathy compared with hydrophilic statins (fluvastatin, pravastatin, and rosuvastatin)."
]
},
" "
]
}
]
}
]
},
